2bwm, a floating window manager that features having two borders

A fast floating WM, with the particularity of having 2 borders, written over
the XCB library and derived from mcwm written by Michael Cardell. In 2bwm
everything is accessible from the keyboard but a pointing device can be used
for move, resize and raise/lower.

Homepage: http://github.com/venam/2bwm/


sxhkd is an optional dependency
if you decide not to use sxhkd, you must replace "sxhkd" with your desired
program in the xinitrc before you run the SlackBuild
